narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Great information about clinical illnesses and physiology, as well as patient relations and patient perspectives. Fantastic class.
Clinical and translational aspects of basic research. Learned how to talk to physician scientists and the kinds of problems that they face on a daily basis. Really great course!

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Strengths: small class, met infrequently but was always quality interaction, little homework, was mostly for our benefit (get what you put in kind of attitude), patient interaction was excellent, Erica is great! Weakness: quality can vary a lot, but it wasn't hard to get the most out of the experience by staying engaged and asking questions!
Excellent course overall. I was very engaged.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yep! MRSP students should look forward to this cornerstone.
